fields.description:
Hi,

Creating this for an add-on developer:

Steps to reproduce
# Send a request to '/rest/api/settings/lookandfeel/custom?spaceKey=XXX
where the lookandfeel data contains a linear-gradient: 
# Request:
{code}
{
"headings":
{ "color":"#333333" }
,
"links":
{ "color":"#3572b0" }
,
"menus":{
"hoverOrFocus":
{ "backgroundColor":"#3572b0" }
,
"color":"#333333"
},
"header":{
"backgroundColor":"rgba(77, 77, 77, 1)",
"button":
{ "backgroundColor":"#3572b0", "color":"#ffffff" }
,
"primaryNavigation":{
"color":"rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72)",
"hoverOrFocus":
{ "backgroundColor":"#3572b0", "color":"#ffffff" }
},
"secondaryNavigation":{
"color":"#333333",
"hoverOrFocus":
{ "backgroundColor":"#3572b0", "color":"#ffffff" }
},
"search":
{ "backgroundColor":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2)", "color":"#ffffff" }
},
"content":{
"screen":{
"background":"#f6f6f6",
"layer":
{ "background":"linear-gradient(rgba(77,101,168,1.00), rgba(80,217,199,1.00))", "width":"100%", "height":"375px" }
,
"gutterTop":"50px",
"gutterRight":"small",
"gutterBottom":"50px",
"gutterLeft":"small"
},
"container":
{ "background":"#FFFFFF", "backgroundColor":"#FFFFFF", "backgroundImage":"none", "backgroundSize":"auto", "padding":"20px", "borderRadius":"0" }
,
"header":
{ "background":"#FFFFFF", "backgroundColor":"#FFFFFF", "backgroundImage":"none", "backgroundSize":"auto", "padding":"30px 30px 10px 30px", "borderRadius":"3px 3px 0 0" }
,
"body":
{ "background":"#FFFFFF", "backgroundColor":"#FFFFFF", "backgroundImage":"none", "backgroundSize":"auto", "padding":"0 30px 30px 30px", "borderRadius":"0 0 3px 3px" }
},
"bordersAndDividers":
{ "color":"#cccccc" }
}
{code}

So I thought maybe it does not work only with gradient so I tested with simple colors like red and does not reflect in the content (page, blog).

Reference DAC: https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/confluence/theme-properties/ (see attached)

Thanks!

Cheers,
Anne Calantog

When replying to an inline comment with original content:

[~ndang] dfasdf

content body expected to be sent through:

{code}
body: "<p><a class="confluence-userlink user-mention current-user-mention" data-username="ndang" href="/wiki/display/~ndang" data-linked-resource-id="11111111" data-linked-resource-version="2" data-linked-resource-type="userinfo" data-base-url="https://pug.jira-dev.com/wiki">Nguyen Dang</a> dfasdf</p>"
{code}

but this is sent instead
{code}
body: "<p><a class="confluence-link" href="http://pug.jira-dev.com/wiki/display/~ndang">Nguyen Dang</a> dfasdf</p>"
{code}

since user metadata is lost, Confluence treats the link as normal link, hence no notification is sent.
